Package de.oth.blocklib.disasters.volcanos

Class VolcanoEruption

java.lang.Object
de.oth.blocklib.disasters.Disaster
de.oth.blocklib.disasters.ChunkAllocatingDisaster
de.oth.blocklib.disasters.volcanos.VolcanoEruption
public class VolcanoEruption
extends ChunkAllocatingDisaster
The VolcanoEruption Disaster. A ChunkAllocatingDisaster that causes a already existing volcano to erupt. The VolcanoManager can be used to find existing volcanos.
Author:
Tobias Mueller

  • Constructor Details

    • VolcanoEruption

      public VolcanoEruption​(VolcanoData data)
      Creates a new VolcanoEruption. Should be added to a DisasterManager, so it gets automatically updated. Should be created on top of a Volcano.
      Parameters:
      data - The VolcanoData of the Volcano that should explode. Can be fetched from the VolcanoManager.

    • VolcanoEruption

      public VolcanoEruption​(org.lwjgl.util.vector.Vector3f topPosition, float craterRadius)
      Creates a new VolcanoEruption. Should be added to a DisasterManager, so it gets automatically updated. Should be created on top of a Volcano.
      Parameters:
      topPosition - the top position of the volcano that should explode.
      craterRadius - the radius of the crater that should be created.
